data Maybe a = Just a | Nothing

instance Monad Maybe where
  return x = Just x
  (Just x) >>= f = f x
  Nothing >>= _ = Nothing
In this implementation, the Maybe type constructor takes a single type parameter a, and the Monad type class provides the functions return and >>= that allow us to combine and transform values of type Maybe a. The return function takes a value of type a and returns a value of type Maybe a, while the >>= function takes a value of type Maybe a and a function from a to Maybe b, and returns a value of type Maybe b. Sure! Here are two monad examples, one in JavaScript and one in C#:

